Subject: occurs in

Subject: results in developmental progression of
Value: p results in the developmental progression of s iff p is a developmental process and s is an anatomical structure and p causes s to undergo a change in state at some point along its natural developmental cycle (this cycle starts with its formation, through the mature structure, and ends with its loss).

Subject: characteristic of part of
Value: q characteristic of part of w if and only if there exists some p such that q inheres in p and p part of w.

Subject: towards
Value: q towards e2 if and only if q is a relational quality such that q inheres-in some e, and e != e2 and q is dependent on e2

Subject: predatory behavior abnormal
Value: (Pristionchus pacificus) Animals exhibit abnormal predatory behavior, compared to controls.

Subject: reduced predatory feeding behavior
Value: (Pristionchus pacificus) Animals exhibit reduced predatory feeding behavior, indicated by reduced predation success, compared to controls.
